{"title_page": "Magnus Persson Atlevi", "text_new": "{{short description|Swedish professional golfer}}\n{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Magnus Persson Atlevi\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = Magnus Persson Atlevi\n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1965|7|26|df=y}} \n| birth_place       = [[Klippan Municipality|Klippan]], [[Sweden]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1971|5|13|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = {{height|m=1.75|precision=0}}\n| weight            = {{convert|75|kg|lb st|abbr=on}}\n| nationality       = {{SWE}}\n| residence         = [[Staffanstorp]], [[Sweden]]\n| spouse            = Elisabeth\n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| yearpro           = 1982\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[European Senior Tour]]\n| extour            = [[European Tour]]<br/>[[Challenge Tour]]\n| prowins           = 12\n| pgawins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour wins -->\n| eurowins          = \n| japwins           = <!-- Number of Japan Golf Tour wins -->\n| asiawins          = <!-- Number of Asian Tour wins -->\n| sunwins           = <!-- Number of Sunshine Tour wins -->\n| auswins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour of Australasia wins -->\n| nwidewins         = <!-- Number of Nationwide Tour wins -->\n| chalwins          = 3\n| champwins         = <!-- Number of Champions Tour wins -->\n| seneurowins       = 2\n| otherwins         = 7\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| masters           = DNP\n| usopen            = DNP\n| open              = T39: 1985\n| pga               = DNP\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = [[Swedish Golfer of the Year]]\n| year1             = 1982\n| award2            = <!-- Achievement or award details -->\n| year2             = <!-- Year(s) of achievement or award -->\n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Magnus Persson Atlevi''' (born 26 July 1965) is a [[List of Swedish professional golfers|Swedish professional golfer]]. He competed as '''Magnus Persson''' until his marriage to Elisabeth Atlevi in 1999.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.parislegendschampionship.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/NOS-12-BIOS-DE-JOUEURS.pdf |title=Paris Legends Championship 2017 Douze Portraits Choises |publisher=www.parislegendschampionship.com |accessdate=30 December 2017 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nAs a golf prodigy, Persson became a scratch player at 15, at the time the youngest ever in [[Sweden]], and reached a +1 handicap at 16, as one of four in the country. Just 15 years of age, Persson finished runner-up and low foreign contestant at the 1980 Orange Bowl International Junior Championship in Coral Gables, [[Florida]], after winning a playoff for second place with [[Stephen Ames]] and [[Paul Way]].<ref>[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/mv0x28qm/popup/1? Tv\u00e5a i v\u00e4rlden - tv\u00e5 \u00e5r f\u00f6r tidigt] (in Swedish) Second in the world, Svensk Golf 1/1981, pp. 6-7</ref> After being a member of the second-placed Sweden amateur team at the [[1982 Eisenhower Trophy|1982]] [[Eisenhower Trophy]] in [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]], and successfully progressing through the 1982 [[European Tour]] [[European Tour Qualifying School|Qualifying School]], Persson turned professional at the age of 17.<ref name=\"chabio\"/> As of early 2016, he still holds the record as the youngest player to win a European Tour card.<ref name=\"senq2016\"/>\n\nHe qualified for the [[1982 Open Championship]] as an amateur, aged 16, and also the following three years, then as a pro. He would go on to start in [[The Open Championship]] eight times.<ref>[http://www.lagk.se/se/shop-pro/vara-tranare Meet the Pro], Lunds Akademiska Golfklubb, accessed 4 March 2016</ref> At the end of 1982, he was named [[Swedish Golfer of the Year]], male and female, by far the youngest player ever and the last time an amateur received the award.\n\nTwice a runner-up on the European Tour, including when he lost out in a playoff to [[Seve Ballesteros]] in the [[Open Renault de Baleares]] in [[1990 European Tour|1990]]. 1990 would become his best season, finishing 30th on the [[European Tour Order of Merit]]. He lost his card at the end of the 1991 season and has since struggled to regain it. In 2001, on his 11th visit to the Qualifying School Finals in as many years, Persson regained his European Tour card.<ref name=\"chabio\">[http://www.europeantour.com/challengetour/players/playerid=152/bio/index.html Challenge Tour Bio], European Tour, accessed 4 March 2016</ref>\n\nPersson won three times on the [[Challenge Tour]], the first title coming in the 1992 [[Perrier European Pro-Am]], the second in the 1993 Torneo Islantilla Golf, and the third in the 1998 Is Molas Challenge.<ref name=\"senq2016\">[http://www.europeantour.com/seniortour/qualifying/season=2016/tournamentid=2016806/news/newsid=287062.html Senior Tour Qualifying School 2016 - Meet The Graduates], European Tour, 29 February 2016</ref>\n\nIn 2009 Persson became Tournament Director of the [[Nordea Tour]]. He has also started to branch out into golf course design, having created one course in Sweden and one in Finland together with his architect father.<ref name=\"chabio\"/>\n\nTurning 50, Persson entered the 2015 Senior Tour Qualifying School. He had a [[European Senior Tour]] card in his grasp before he four-putted the final green for a double bogey, missing out by one shot. He secured his card for the [[2016 European Senior Tour]] tying for third in the 2016 Senior Tour Qualifying School, having led the field after rounds two and three.<ref name=\"senq2016\"/>\nPersson won the 2016 [[Paris Legends Championship]] and went on to finished second on the [[2016 European Senior Tour#Leading money winners|2016 European Senior Tour Order of Merit]]. In 2018, he finished runner-up at the [[Staysure PGA Seniors Championship]], the oldest important seniors tournament in Europe, before winning the [[European Tour Properties Senior Classic]].\n\n==Professional wins (12)==\n===Challenge Tour wins (3)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runner(s)-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|30 Aug [[1992 Challenge Tour|1992]]\n|[[Perrier European Pro-Am]]\n|\u22123 (74-69-70=213)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Mathias Gr\u00f6nberg]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|2 May 1993\n|[[Torneo Istantilla Golf]]\n|\u22125 (70-73-70-70=283)\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Antonio Garrido (golfer)|Antonio Garrido]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|5 Apr 1998\n|[[Is Molas Challenge]]\n|\u22125 (69-71-69-74=283)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thomas Levet]], {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Christophe Pottier]]\n|}\n===Swedish Golf Tour/Nordic Golf league wins (4)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!! Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runner-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|24 Aug 1986\n|[[PGA Club Sweden Open]]<ref>[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/g7j2hx1q/popup/1? PGA Club Sweden Open] (in Swedish) Svensk Golf 9/1986, pp. 24, 25, 77</ref>\n| -3 (71-67-70-77=285)\n|Playoff\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} Magnus Grankvist\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|28 Sept 1986\n|Owell Open<ref name=\":0\">[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/2qp1v96n/popup/1? Owell Open] (in Swedish) Svensk Golf 11/1986, pp. 42, 43, 71</ref>\n|<nowiki>-2 (67-73-68=208)</nowiki>\n|6 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anders Forsbrand]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3\n|21 Sept 2008\n|Visma Masters (Ecco Tour)\n|<nowiki>-11 (71-68-66=205)</nowiki>\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|FIN}}Toni Hakula\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |4\n|18 Sept 2010\n|[[PEAB PGA Open]]\n| +3 (71-71-77=219)\n|4 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} Mark Larsson\n|}\n''Note: [[Nordic Golf League]] established 1999 consisting primarily of tournaments on the national tours of Denmark (Ecco Tour) and Sweden (Swedish Golf Tour)''\n\n===Other wins (3)===\n*2009 Sval\u00f6v Open (Swedish Minitour)\n*2011 Guldpokalen (Swedish Minitour)\n*2013 Swedish PGA Club Pro Championship<ref>[https://www.pgasweden.com/tavlingskalender/vw-pga-open-club-pro-masterskapen/pga-club-pro-masterskapen-tidigare-vinnare/ Swedish PGA Club Pro Championship, Tidigare vinnare] (in Swedish) Swedish PGA, Former winners</ref>\n\n===European Senior Tour wins (2)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.\n!Date\n!Tournament\n!Winning score\n!Margin of<br>victory\n!Runner(s)-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|11 Sep [[2016 European Senior Tour|2016]]\n|[[Paris Legends Championship]]\n|\u22128 (70-66-69=205)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Stephen Dodd]], {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Philip Golding]],<br>{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Mark Mouland]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|9 Sep [[2018 European Senior Tour|2018]]\n|[[European Tour Properties Senior Classic]]\n|\u221214 (66-66-67=199)\n|3 strokes\n|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Stephen Dodd]]\n|}\n\n==Playoff record==\n'''European Tour playoff record (0\u20132)'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Year!!Tournament!!Opponent!!Result\n|-style=\"background:#F2C1D1;\"\n|align=center|1\n|[[1987 European Tour|1987]]\n|[[Scandinavian Enterprise Open]]\n|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Gordon Brand, Jnr]]\n|Lost to birdie on first extra hole\n|-style=\"background:#F2C1D1;\"\n|align=center|2\n|[[1990 European Tour|1990]]\n|[[Open Renault de Baleares]]\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Seve Ballesteros]]\n|Lost to par on first extra hole\n|}\n\n'''PGA Tour of Australasia playoff record (0\u20131)'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Year!!Tournament!!Opponent!!Result\n|-style=\"background:#F2C1D1;\"\n|align=center|1\n|1986\n|[[Tasmanian Open|Foster's Tasmanian Open]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Stewart Ginn]]\n|Lost on second extra hole\n|}\n\n==Results in major championships==\n{| cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 95%; border: #aaa solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"\n!align=\"left\"|Tournament\n!1982\n!1983\n!1984\n!1985\n!1986\n!1987\n!1988\n!1989\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Open Championship]]\n|CUT\n|CUT\n|CUT\n|T39\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|CUT\n|CUT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|}\n{| cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 95%; border: #aaa solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"\n!align=\"left\"|Tournament\n!1990\n!1991\n!1992\n!1993\n!1994\n!1995\n!1996\n!1997\n!1998\n!1999\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Open Championship]]\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|T101\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|}\n{| cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 95%; border: #aaa solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"\n!align=\"left\"|Tournament\n!2000\n!2001\n!2002\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Open Championship]]\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|CUT\n|}\n''Note: Persson Atlevi only played in The Open Championship.''\n{{legend|#eeeeee|Did not play}}\nCUT = missed the half-way cut (3rd round cut in 1984 Open Championship)<br>\n\"T\" = tied\n\n==Team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[European Youths' Team Championship]] (representing Sweden): 1981, 1982\n*[[St Andrews Trophy]] (representing the Continent of Europe): 1982 (winners)\n*[[Eisenhower Trophy]] (representing Sweden): [[1982 Eisenhower Trophy|1982]]<ref>[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/1pfc350j/popup/1?  Golf - Den stora sporten] [Golf - The great sport] (in Swedish). Swedish Golf Federation. 2004. p. 182, 184, 199</ref>\n\n'''Professional'''\n*[[Hennessy Cognac Cup]] (representing Sweden): 1984\n*[[Alfred Dunhill Cup]] (representing Sweden): [[1988 Dunhill Cup|1988]], [[1989 Dunhill Cup|1989]], [[1990 Dunhill Cup|1990]]\n*[[World Cup of Golf|World Cup]] (representing Sweden): [[1983 World Cup (men's golf)|1983]], [[1984 World Cup (men's golf)|1984]], [[1990 World Cup (men's golf)|1990]]\n*[[Europcar Cup]] (representing Sweden): 1988 (winners)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{EuroTour player|152}}\n*{{OWGR|315}}\n*[http://www.golfdata.se/guide/guidea.asp?nr=204 Profile at golfdata.se] {{in lang|sv}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Persson Atlevi, Magnus}}\n[[Category:Swedish male golfers]]\n[[Category:European Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:European Senior Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:People from Staffanstorp Municipality]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swedish professional golfer}}\n{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Magnus Persson Atlevi\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = Magnus Persson Atlevi\n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1965|7|26|df=y}} \n| birth_place       = [[Klippan Municipality|Klippan]], [[Sweden]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1971|5|13|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = {{height|m=1.75|precision=0}}\n| weight            = {{convert|75|kg|lb st|abbr=on}}\n| nationality       = {{SWE}}\n| residence         = [[Staffanstorp]], [[Sweden]]\n| spouse            = Elisabeth\n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| yearpro           = 1982\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[European Senior Tour]]\n| extour            = [[European Tour]]<br/>[[Challenge Tour]]\n| prowins           = 12\n| pgawins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour wins -->\n| eurowins          = \n| japwins           = <!-- Number of Japan Golf Tour wins -->\n| asiawins          = <!-- Number of Asian Tour wins -->\n| sunwins           = <!-- Number of Sunshine Tour wins -->\n| auswins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour of Australasia wins -->\n| nwidewins         = <!-- Number of Nationwide Tour wins -->\n| chalwins          = 3\n| champwins         = <!-- Number of Champions Tour wins -->\n| seneurowins       = 2\n| otherwins         = 7\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| masters           = DNP\n| usopen            = DNP\n| open              = T39: 1985\n| pga               = DNP\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = [[Swedish Golfer of the Year]]\n| year1             = 1982\n| award2            = <!-- Achievement or award details -->\n| year2             = <!-- Year(s) of achievement or award -->\n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Magnus Persson Atlevi''' (born 26 July 1965) is a [[List of Swedish professional golfers|Swedish professional golfer]]. He competed as '''Magnus Persson''' until his marriage to Elisabeth Atlevi in 1999.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.parislegendschampionship.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/NOS-12-BIOS-DE-JOUEURS.pdf |title=Paris Legends Championship 2017 Douze Portraits Choises |publisher=www.parislegendschampionship.com |accessdate=30 December 2017 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nAs a golf prodigy, Persson became a scratch player at 15, at the time the youngest ever in [[Sweden]], and reached a +1 handicap at 16, as one of four in the country. Just 15 years of age, Persson finished runner-up and low foreign contestant at the 1980 Orange Bowl International Junior Championship in Coral Gables, [[Florida]], after winning a playoff for second place with [[Stephen Ames]] and [[Paul Way]].<ref>[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/mv0x28qm/popup/1? Tv\u00e5a i v\u00e4rlden - tv\u00e5 \u00e5r f\u00f6r tidigt] (in Swedish) Second in the world, Svensk Golf 1/1981, pp. 6-7</ref> After being a member of the second-placed Sweden amateur team at the [[1982 Eisenhower Trophy|1982]] [[Eisenhower Trophy]] in [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]], and successfully progressing through the 1982 [[European Tour]] [[European Tour Qualifying School|Qualifying School]], Persson turned professional at the age of 17.<ref name=\"chabio\"/> As of early 2016, he still holds the record as the youngest player to win a European Tour card.<ref name=\"senq2016\"/>\n\nHe qualified for the [[1982 Open Championship]] as an amateur, aged 16, and also the following three years, then as a pro. He would go on to start in [[The Open Championship]] eight times.<ref>[http://www.lagk.se/se/shop-pro/vara-tranare Meet the Pro], Lunds Akademiska Golfklubb, accessed 4 March 2016</ref> At the end of 1982, he was named [[Swedish Golfer of the Year]], male and female, by far the youngest player ever and the last time an amateur received the award.\n\nTwice a runner-up on the European Tour, including when he lost out in a playoff to [[Seve Ballesteros]] in the [[Open Renault de Baleares]] in [[1990 European Tour|1990]]. 1990 would become his best season, finishing 30th on the [[European Tour Order of Merit]]. He lost his card at the end of the 1991 season and has since struggled to regain it. In 2001, on his 11th visit to the Qualifying School Finals in as many years, Persson regained his European Tour card.<ref name=\"chabio\">[http://www.europeantour.com/challengetour/players/playerid=152/bio/index.html Challenge Tour Bio], European Tour, accessed 4 March 2016</ref>\n\nPersson won three times on the [[Challenge Tour]], the first title coming in the 1992 [[Perrier European Pro-Am]], the second in the 1993 Torneo Islantilla Golf, and the third in the 1998 Is Molas Challenge.<ref name=\"senq2016\">[http://www.europeantour.com/seniortour/qualifying/season=2016/tournamentid=2016806/news/newsid=287062.html Senior Tour Qualifying School 2016 - Meet The Graduates], European Tour, 29 February 2016</ref>\n\nIn 2009 Persson became Tournament Director of the [[Nordea Tour]]. He has also started to branch out into golf course design, having created one course in Sweden and one in Finland together with his architect father.<ref name=\"chabio\"/>\n\nTurning 50, Persson entered the 2015 Senior Tour Qualifying School. He had a [[European Senior Tour]] card in his grasp before he four-putted the final green for a double bogey, missing out by one shot. He secured his card for the [[2016 European Senior Tour]] tying for third in the 2016 Senior Tour Qualifying School, having led the field after rounds two and three.<ref name=\"senq2016\"/>\nPersson won the 2016 [[Paris Legends Championship]] and went on to finished second on the [[2016 European Senior Tour#Leading money winners|2016 European Senior Tour Order of Merit]]. In 2018, he finished runner-up at the [[Staysure PGA Seniors Championship]], the oldest important seniors tournament in Europe, before winning the [[European Tour Properties Senior Classic]].\n\n==Professional wins (12)==\n===Challenge Tour wins (3)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runner(s)-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|30 Aug [[1992 Challenge Tour|1992]]\n|[[Perrier European Pro-Am]]\n|\u22123 (74-69-70=213)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Mathias Gr\u00f6nberg]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|2 May 1993\n|[[Torneo Istantilla Golf]]\n|\u22125 (70-73-70-70=283)\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Antonio Garrido (golfer)|Antonio Garrido]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|5 Apr 1998\n|[[Is Molas Challenge]]\n|\u22125 (69-71-69-74=283)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thomas Levet]], {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Christophe Pottier]]\n|}\n===Swedish Golf Tour/Nordic Golf league wins (4)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!! Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runner-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|24 Aug 1986\n|[[PGA Club Sweden Open]]<ref>[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/g7j2hx1q/popup/1? PGA Club Sweden Open] (in Swedish) Svensk Golf 9/1986, pp. 24, 25, 77</ref>\n| -3 (71-67-70-77=285)\n|Playoff\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} Magnus Grankvist\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|28 Sept 1986\n|Owell Open<ref name=\":0\">[http://www.e-magin.se/paper/2qp1v96n/popup/1? Owell Open] (in Swedish) Svensk Golf 11/1986, pp. 42, 43, 71</ref>\n|<nowiki>-2 (67-73-68=208)</nowiki>\n|6 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anders Forsbrand]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3\n|21 Sept 2008\n|Visma Masters (Ecco Tour)\n|<nowiki>-11 (71-68-66=205)</nowiki>\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|FIN}}Toni Hakula\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |4\n|18 Sept 2010\n|[[PEAB PGA Open]]\n| +3 (71-71-77=219)\n|4 strokes\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} Mark Larsson\n|}\n''Note: [[Nordic Golf League]] established 1999 consisting primarily of tournaments on the national tours of Denmark (Ecco Tour) and Sweden (Swedish Golf Tour)''\n\n===Other wins (3)===\n*2009 Sval\u00f6v Open (Swedish Minitour)\n*2011 Guldpokalen (Swedish Minitour)\n*2013 Swedish PGA Club Pro Championship<ref>[https://www.pgasweden.com/tavlingskalender/vw-pga-open-club-pro-masterskapen/pga-club-pro-masterskapen-tidigare-vinnare/ Swedish PGA Club Pro Championship, Tidigare vinnare] (in Swedish) Swedish PGA, Former winners</ref>\n\n===European Senior Tour wins (2)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.\n!Date\n!Tournament\n!Winning score\n!Margin of<br>victory\n!Runner(s)-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|11 Sep [[2016 European Senior Tour|2016]]\n|[[Paris Legends Championship]]\n|\u22128 (70-66-69=205)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Stephen Dodd]], {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Philip Golding]],<br>{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Mark Mouland]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|9 Sep [[2018 European Senior Tour|2018]]\n|[[European Tour Properties Senior Cla