s\" \u2013 1975, Island\n*\"[[Si Tu Dois Partir]]\"/\"White Dress\" \u2013 August 1975\n*\"Jams O'Donnell's Jig\"/\"The Last Waltz\" \u2013 June 1978\n*\"Rubber Band\"/\"The Bonny Black Hare\" \u2013 March 1980\n*\"Quazi-Be-Goode\"/\"Where Would You Rather Be Tonight?\" \u2013 August 1986\n*\"Meet on the Ledge\"/\"Sigh Beg Sigh Mor\" \u2013 May 1987\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071016090206/http://richardthompson-music.com/album.asp?id=65 Richard Thompson Site]\n*[http://www.informatik.uni-hamburg.de/~zierke/sandy.denny/records/fcsingles.html Sandy Denny singles]\n*{{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409235917/http://www.fcfansite.fsnet.co.uk/ |date=April 9, 2016 |title=Fan site }}\n*[http://www.slipcue.com/music/international/celtic/artists/fairport.html Online Discography]\n*[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p4222/discography|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic Discography]\n\n{{Fairport Convention}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of British artists]]\n[[Category:Folk music discographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2013}}\n[[Folk rock]] group [[Fairport Convention]] is usually credited as the first [[British folk rock]] band. Unfortunately for the band, folk rock is bad and their band sucked. Founded in 1967 and initially covering songs by artists such as [[Bob Dylan]] and [[Joni Mitchell]], they developed a devoted niche following by providing [[Electric guitar|electrified]] and upbeat versions of traditional folk tunes alongside their own compositions. In a career spanning over fifty years, notable for numerous changes of line-up as well as continued success, Fairport Convention have issued over fifty albums.\n\n==Albums==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:75%; font-size:1em;\"\n! style=\"background-color: LightBlue;   color: Black; font-weight: bold; text-align: center; width:15%\" | Release date\n! style=\"background-c